14. a3{ White's idea is to play  b4  quickly, to open up the position a bit and soften our pawns. }
14. d4{ Of course, we are not threatening to take White's knight on  c3 , as our d-pawn is pinned, but with this move, we alleviate the pressure on our d-pawn, so we can finally move our  e7 -knight and continue development. }
15. b4{ White continues with their plan. }
15. Ng6{ With this move, we enable ourselves to recapture with the bishop on  c5 . Furthermore, we can now also just develop the bishop (to  e7  for example) so we can castle afterwards. White will need to act quickly here, as otherwise, they will just be down a pawn for insufficient compensation. }
