11. Nc3{ White just continues development. }
11. d5{ A crucial move, as this will make it much easier for us to develop. }
12. Qa4{ The best square for White's queen, as the pin on our  c6 -knight gives some tactical possibilities. }
12. Qd7{ Neutralizing the pin on our knight and freeing up the  d8 -square for our rook. }
13. Rd1{ White brings the rook into the game and increases the pressure on our  d5 -pawn. }
13. Rd8{ We should bring our rook into the game as well, to add some support to the  d5 -pawn. }
14. Bf4{ This was played in one correspondence game. White is planning  Nb5 , which would create some devastating threats. }
14. d4( { Alleviating the pressure on our d-pawn. With this move, we also create a strong response to }15.Nb5 { . } )
