16. Rb8( { The position is still quite messy, but Black is doing fine in the complications. For example, if }17.Qxa7 { , we can opt for }17...Nc6 18.Bxc6 dxc6 { followed by ... f6 , when the engine indicates the (in)famous 0.00.    In case you feel more adventurous, }{   }17...Qd8 { is also an option. }18.f4 Bxg5! { , and now taking back }19.fxg5 { is well met by }19...Qc7 { , }{ which wasn't working before with the bishop on  e7  in view of  Nd5 . } )
