19. Rd1{ White's only reasonable move. }
19. d4{ We sacrifice the exchange, but we further disturb the harmony in White's position. }
20. Ne4{ This can get very tricky. }
20. Nxe4{ We absolutely have to trade the knights. }
21. Bxe4{ After this recapture, White is threatening checkmate on  h7 , which is actually not that easy to defend against. }
21. h5{ The only good way to defend against White's checkmate threat on  h7 . Black is fine though in the complications. A line that is important to be aware of is the following one: }
22. Bxa8
22. Qxa8
23. Qxh5
23. Re8{ White is already lost, as they are struggling to defend the  e2 -pawn and Black's initiative is crushing. }
24. Qf3
24. Qc8{ Avoiding the queen trade. Black is crushing here due to White's weak light squares around the king.     The ideas of ... Bxe2  and ... Bb7  combined with ... Qh3  are too much for White to handle. Stockfish already evaluates this position as -4 (and probably even more if you let it run). }
