20. Qc1{ White's best move. By using a clever tactic, White clears the  d1 -square for the rook. }
20. Qe7{ Of course, we are not interested in any trades. }
21. Rd1
21. e5{ We can now start using our e-pawn to create serious counterplay. }
22. a3{ White's only move to avoid getting in trouble. }
22. Bc5{ The most active square for our bishop. }
23. b4{ White can also continue challenging our dark-squared bishop. }
23. Bd4
24. Ra2
24. Qe6{ The most accurate. Our queen is headed to  f5 , from where it will cause White a lot of trouble. }
25. Rad2
25. Qf5
26. Rxd4{ White absolutely has to return the exchange sooner or later, as otherwise, our initiative would become too strong. }
26. exd4( 26...Qxf3? { unfortunately does not work due to }27.Nd2± { . } )
27. Qf4{ White's best move, trading off our active queen on  f5 . }
27. Qxf4
28. gxf4
28. Rd8{ Black is fine in this endgame. Next, we will play ... Kf8  to bring our king a bit closer to the center and to make sure that we never have any back-rank issues. }
