13. Qc2{ With this move, White is preparing the idea of  Bf4  followed by  Ne5 / d2 , without allowing ... Ne4 . }
13. b5{ We continue with our plan, cementing the bishop on  c4 . }
14. Bf4{ White continues with their plan, preparing  Nd2  or  Ne5  to exert pressure on the  c4 -bishop. }
14. a5{ The logical follow-up, exerting pressure on the  b4 -pawn. White has to react energetically here, as otherwise, they are just worse. }
