14. Nh5{ Discouraging White from playing  f4 , as now the  g3 -pawn would start hanging immediately. }
15. f4{ This move has also been played by some strong players, but it is not one to be concerned about at all, as Black has a lot of good options to choose from here. }
15. Nd7{ I suggest this move, as I believe it to be the simplest. Black does not sacrifice any material and gets a fine position, as White has created a lot of weaknesses for themselves. }( { Black is also fine in the complications starting with }15...Nxg3 { . } )
16. Kh2{ The only proper way to defend the  g3 -pawn. }
16. Bxc3{ Somewhat surprisingly, we give up our dark-squared bishop for the knight, but we will soon see why. }
17. bxc3
