14. Kh7{ It is important to address the threat on the pawn on  h6  this way instead of ... h5  so that we can meet a potential  Bf4  with ... Nh5 . Next up, we are going to play ... Nbd7  and we will have a good game.    You might have noticed by now that we have two ways to protect the pawn on  h6 : either with ... Kh7  or by playing ... h5 . Generally, when the knight is on  e1 , we can rely on ... Kh7  as a defensive mechanism since the  f3  break is no longer as powerful. Without a knight on  h2  to pressure our  g4 -pawn and support a further  g3 - g4  from White, we can keep the ... Nh5  jump in reserve and control the dark squares better by maintaining the pawn on  h6 .    When the white knight is on  h2 , however, ... h5  not only takes the sting out of  f3  but also makes sure the  h2 -knight will need some time to get back into the game. }
