12. Bf5{ The advantage of having played ... g5  is that now White cannot play  Nh4  to push our  f5 -bishop back. }
13. h4{ White's critical continuation. White tries to chip away at our kingside pawn structure, so our response is forced. }
13. g4{ Pushing the knight back and keeping our pawn structure somewhat intact. }
