1. d4
1. Nf6
2. c4
2. e6
3. g3{ With this move, White intends to play the Catalan and at the same time avoids the Queen's Indian. However, it does allow another option. }
3. c5{ The point of this repertoire is to avoid the annoying Catalan and to get fighting positions. This move offers just what we are looking for. Black is not only fine in the  g3  Benoni, but it also offers Black plenty of fighting chances in the arising positions. }
4. Nf3( { White's only reasonable option if they want to avoid the  g3  Benoni. With this move, White is keeping the position somewhat safe and is avoiding the double-edged positions we saw after }4.d5 { . However, this move does have quite some venom to it and we should therefore play accurately. } )
4. cxd4
5. Nxd4
5. d5{ The game becomes somewhat of a reversed Grünfeld now. It is important that we delay playing ... Nc6 , as then White can always trade their knight on  d4  for our knight. }
6. Bg2
6. e5{ Now, White is forced to retreat. }
7. Nc2{ This has been played by some strong players, including Vallejo Pons. Therefore, it is important to be familiar with this move as well. }
7. d4{ Once again, we address White's threat on our  d5 -pawn by just pushing it forward and grabbing more space in the center. }
8. f4( { White should exert pressure on our center as quickly as possible, as otherwise, they are just worse already. Black is already better after }8.O-O Nc6⩱ { . } )
8. Nc6{ Our best move, developing the knight and adding some support to our center. }
9. Bxc6+{ This is White's most popular continuation. White wins a pawn but at the cost of weakening the light squares severely. }
9. bxc6
10. fxe5
10. Qa5+{ The most accurate, as this move allows us to keep the queens on the board. }
11. Qd2{ White's best way to block the check, as now they can still take the  d4 -pawn with the queen. }
11. Qxe5
12. Qxd4
12. Qf5{ Despite being down a pawn, Black is better here due to the fact that White's king does not have a safe haven. Next, we will continue our development with ... Be7  and ... O-O , and Black will be having a pleasant initiative. }
