3. c5{ This is the way to go. Since White does not have a pawn on  c4 , White cannot meet this move with  d5 . }
4. Bg2
4. cxd4
5. Nxd4
5. d5
6. O-O( 6.c4 { would transpose to the  Benoni Declined  chapter. } )
6. e5
