7. Be6{ This is the right way to continue our development. We are going to delay ... Nc6 , as we want to be able to meet  Bg5  with ... Nbd7 . }( { The natural-looking }7...Nc6 { would be inaccurate, as here White has }8.Bg5 Be6 9.Nc3 { , with nagging pressure on our center. } )
8. Nc3
8. Be7
9. f4{ White's best approach to exert pressure on Black's center. White is not only threatening to play  fxe5  but also  f5  to kick the bishop away. }
9. exf4
10. gxf4{ The critical continuation. White still wants to play  f5  to kick the bishop away so that the  d5 -pawn becomes weak. }( { After }10.Bxf4 { , we will just play }10...O-O= { followed }{ by ... Nc6  and Black has nothing to worry about. } )
