4. c5( { A typical move, challenging White's center and gaining a bit of space. Starting with }4...d5 { followed by ... c5  is fine as well, and will likely lead to the same thing. } )
5. e3{ White strengthens their center and also prepares to develop their light-squared bishop. }
5. d5( { Black can also decide to go after the  b2 -pawn with }5...Qb6 { or }5...cxd4 6.exd4 Qb6 { , but I like the text better, as it is a much easier way of playing against the Torre. } )
6. Nbd2{ White continues development with this natural move. }
6. Nbd7{ Somewhat counterintuitively, the knight is actually better placed here than on  c6 , as now we are better equipped to deal with a potential  e4  push from White. This is because after a potential  e4   dxe4   Nxe4 , our  d7 -knight defends the  f6 -knight and the pawn on  c5 . }
7. c3{ White further strengthens the  d4 -pawn and aims to develop the bishop to  d3 , as now they will be able to meet a potential ... c4  with  Bc2 . }
7. Bd6{ The best-developing square for our dark-squared bishop, as here it also fights for the control of the  e5 -square. }
8. Bd3{ Vice versa, this is the most active developing square for White's light-squared bishop. }
8. O-O{ We continue our development. }
9. O-O{ White just continues development as well. }
9. b6{ With this move, we aim to develop our light-squared bishop to  b7 , as it will make it more difficult for White to achieve the  e4  push. }
10. Qe2{ White slightly improves the placement of their queen before starting any complications in the center. }
10. Bb7{ We just stick to our plan and develop our bishop. }
11. e4( { Here we have to react somewhat differently compared to  10.e4 , as in this position, White can meet }11...cxd4? { with }12.e5 { and win a piece. }{ If White does not play  e4 , we will just play ... Qc7 , and we will have nothing to worry about whatsoever. } )
11. dxe4{ We have to take this pawn, as White was threatening  e5 . }
12. Nxe4
12. Be7{ If White takes with the knight on  f6 , we should recapture with the bishop to free our pieces somewhat. Some trades are inevitable here and Black is completely fine. }
